    "output_index": 0,
    "content_index": 0,
    "text": "The connected MongoDB instance contains the following databases:\n\n1. **admin** – The built-in administrative database used for user authentication and administrative operations.\n2. **config** – The configuration database, typically used in sharded clusters to store shard metadata.\n3. **local** – The local database that stores instance-specific data, such as the `startup_log` collection and replica set information.\n\nThese are the three default/system databases that come pre-installed with any MongoDB instance. No additional custom databases have been created yet.",
